  "prompt": "Instagram (product): How do I quickly unfollow people on Instagram?",
  "response": "Unfollowing multiple accounts on Instagram can help streamline your feed and improve your overall experience on the platform. While Instagram doesn\u2019t offer a native bulk unfollow feature to prevent spam and ensure genuine interactions, there are efficient methods you can use within the app and on the web to unfollow people more quickly. Below are some strategies you can employ:\n\n## **Using the Instagram Mobile App**\n\n### **1. Unfollow via Your Profile**\n1. **Open the Instagram App:** Launch Instagram on your mobile device and log in to your account if you haven\u2019t already.\n2. **Go to Your Profile:** Tap on your profile picture in the bottom right corner.\n3. **Access the Following List:** Tap on the number of people you\u2019re following, which is located below your bio.\n4. **Scroll Through the List:** As you scroll, you'll see a list of all the accounts you follow.\n5. **Unfollow Accounts:**\n   - **For Each Account:** Next to each account\u2019s name, you\u2019ll see a \"Following\" button.\n   - **Tap \"Following\":** Tapping this button will change it to \"Follow,\" indicating that you\u2019ve unfollowed the account.\n6. **Repeat as Needed:** Continue scrolling and tapping \"Following\" to unfollow additional accounts.\n\n### **2. Use the \"Least Interacted With\" Feature (If Available)**\nInstagram occasionally rolls out features that help users manage their following list based on interaction:\n1. **Navigate to Your Following List:** As described above.\n2. **Look for Filters or Sorting Options:** If Instagram has introduced a sorting feature like \"Least Interacted With,\" use it to find accounts you rarely engage with.\n3. **Unfollow Accordingly:** Use the \"Following\" button to unfollow those accounts.\n\n*Note: Feature availability may vary based on updates and your region.*\n\n## **Using Instagram on a Web Browser**\n\nAccessing Instagram via a web browser on your computer can sometimes make the unfollowing process faster due to larger screen space and easier navigation.\n\n1. **Visit Instagram.com:** Open your preferred web browser and go to [instagram.com](https://www.instagram.com).\n2. **Log In to Your Account:** Enter your credentials to access your profile.\n3. **Go to Your Following List:** Click on your profile picture in the top right, select \"Profile,\" then click on \"Following.\"\n4. **Unfollow Accounts:**\n   - **Hover Over the \"Following\" Button:** It will change to \"Unfollow.\"\n   - **Click \"Unfollow\":** Confirm if prompted.\n5. **Repeat:** Continue this process for each account you wish to unfollow.\n\n*Using a desktop can sometimes allow for quicker navigation compared to the mobile app.*\n\n## **Considerations and Best Practices**\n\n- **Avoid Mass Unfollowing Quickly:** Instagram monitors unfollow activity to prevent spam. Unfollowing too many accounts in a short period may temporarily restrict your ability to follow/unfollow.\n- **Review Regularly:** Periodically review the accounts you follow to ensure your feed remains relevant and engaging.\n- **Use Lists or Notes:** If you have a list of accounts you'd like to unfollow, keep it handy (e.g., in a notes app) to streamline the process.\n\n## **Third-Party Tools and Cautions**\n\nWhile there are third-party applications and services that claim to offer bulk unfollow capabilities, **caution is strongly advised**:\n\n- **Security Risks:** Providing your Instagram credentials to third-party apps can compromise your account security.\n- **Violation of Instagram\u2019s Terms of Service:** Using unauthorized tools can lead to your account being restricted or banned.\n- **Data Privacy Concerns:** Third-party services may misuse your personal data.\n\n**Recommendation:** Stick to Instagram\u2019s official app and website for managing your following list to ensure the safety and integrity of your account.\n\n## **Conclusion**\n\nWhile Instagram doesn\u2019t support bulk unfollowing natively, using the methods outlined above can help you efficiently manage the accounts you follow. Regularly curating your following list ensures a more personalized and enjoyable Instagram experience. Always prioritize the security of your account by avoiding unauthorized third-party tools.\n\nIf you need further assistance or have specific questions, feel free to ask!",
